Supports flexibilty using Polymorphism.
-----------------------------------------
Its greek word, poly(many) morphs(forms).
 The ability of same function or behaviuor to be present in multiple forms is called polymorphism. 
 EX: upskillhouseprograms\src\main\java\org\example\oops\polymorphism\PolymorhDemo.java

Two types
  Compile Time polymorphism(Method Overloading) - Same behaviour different forms.
     These Methods will reside in same class.
     The arguments will be different.
     The method name and return type will be same.

     The method resolution(which method to be picked among differnt methods of same behaviour) will happen during compiletime itself.

    EX: 
    public String joinInfo(String info1, String info2, String info3){
        return info1 + info2 + info3;
    }

    public String joinInfo(String info1, String info2){
        return info1 + info2;
    }
      . 
  Runtime Polymorphism(Method Overriding).
  ---------------------------------------- 
     These Methods will reside in different class.
     The arguments will be same.
     The method name and return type will be same.

     The method resolution(which method to be picked among differnt methods of same behaviour) will happen during Runtime.

